# EvairSIM H5 — Project Overview

## What This Is
A mobile-first H5 web app for selling and managing eSIMs and physical SIM cards. Customers purchase eSIM plans, activate physical SIMs, top up data, and manage their SIMs. Hosted on Netlify.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Vite + React + TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS (utility-first, mobile-first)
- **Hosting**: Netlify (auto-deploys from GitHub)
- **Serverless**: Netlify Functions (in `netlify/functions/`)
- **eSIM Supplier**: ESIMAccess (Red Tea) API — proxied through Netlify functions
- **Email**: Resend API (via `netlify/functions/send-esim-email.mjs`)
- **i18n**: react-i18next (en, zh, es) — all user-facing strings must use `t()` keys
- **Barcode scanning**: html5-qrcode library
- **Icons**: Lucide React

## Key File Structure
```
App.tsx              — Root component, global state, tab navigation, previousTab ref for back nav
views/ShopView.tsx   — eSIM purchase: Single Country / Multi-Country browse modes, popular countries first
views/MySimsView.tsx — SIM management, top-up, data usage donut, physical SIM status
views/PhysicalSimSetupView.tsx — 3-step SIM binding wizard (Scan → Confirm → Done), login gate
views/ProductTab.tsx — Tab container routing between Shop, MySims, PhysicalSim
views/ProfileView.tsx — Profile menu, share (Web Share API), star rating popup, sub-views
views/LoginModal.tsx — Auth modal (login + registration)
views/ECardView.tsx  — eSIM card detail view
views/ContactUsView.tsx — AI-powered contact support
views/InboxView.tsx  — Notifications inbox
services/dataService.ts — UNIFIED API abstraction layer (留口子) — ALL components import from here
services/esimApi.ts  — ESIMAccess (Red Tea) supplier API wrapper
services/api/esim.ts — Backend API client (placeholder, for future use)
types.ts             — Shared TypeScript interfaces
i18n/en.ts, zh.ts, es.ts — Translations (English, Chinese, Spanish)
hooks/useEdgeSwipeBack.ts — iOS-like swipe gesture
```

## UI/UX Decisions
- Brand color: `#FF6600` (orange), referred to as `brand-orange` in Tailwind
- Brand gradient: `linear-gradient(135deg, #FF6600 0%, #FF8A3D 100%)`
- Logo / wordmarks:
  - **Boot splash** (`BootSplash`): **`/public/evairsim-splash-logo.png`** — transparent horizontal EvairSIM mark only. Never swap in `evairsim-logo.jpg/png` banners or screenshot mock-ups unless Jordan replaces this file deliberately.
  - Other surfaces: `/public/evairsim-logo.png`, `/evairsim-wordmark.png`, etc., as wired today.
- No bottom navigation bar (removed — blocked too much screen area). Uses top SIM Card / eSIM toggle instead.
- All sub-views support swipe-from-left-edge to go back
- Back navigation from Contact Us / Inbox uses `previousTab` ref to return to correct origin tab
- Sample name placeholder: "John Smith" (not real user name)
- App version shown in Profile: v2.9.0
- **Page spacing**: `.pt-safe` class in `app.css` provides 12px top padding on mobile, 1.25rem on desktop, `env(safe-area-inset-top)` in standalone PWA. All headers use this class consistently.
- **Navigation persistence**: `activeTab`, `currentSimType`, and `viewMode` saved to sessionStorage so pull-to-refresh returns to the same screen.
- **Install eSIM UX**: No large center block. Uninstalled eSIMs show blue "Install" badge + "Tap to install" subtitle on banner card. Tapping opens install modal directly. One-time install warning shown at top of modal.
- **Delete SIM**: Proceeds with local removal even if backend API unbind fails (expected for demo/test SIMs).

## Business Rules
- **Physical SIM cards**: Only US data plans sold currently
- **eSIMs**: All countries available (207 countries, 2,489+ packages)
- **Top-up plans**: Filtered to 30/60/90/180 day plans only. Pricing ~100% markup rounded to X.99
- **Share URL**: `https://evairdigital.com`
- **Support email**: `service@evairdigital.com`
